                <head>215. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Migratory Labor agreement between Mexico and the United States, which entered
                    into force on August 11, 1951, was extended <pb facs="0732" n="698"
                        xml:id="pg_698"/> to December 31, 1956, by exchange of notes between Mexican
                    Foreign Minister Padilla Nervo and Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WF2"
                        >White</persName> on December 23 in Mexico City. For text of the Migratory
                    Labor agreement of August 11, 1951, see <hi rend="italic">United States Treaties
                        and Other International Agreements</hi> (UST) 1951, volume 2 (part 2), page
                    1940. For text of the notes extending the agreement, see 6 UST (pt. 5) 6058.
                    Documentation on the subject is in Department of State, Central File
                    811.06(M).</p>
            </div>
